          ],
          moraleTitle: "Мораль, удача и сила стека",
          moraleItems: [
              "Мораль - от -20 до +20. Каждый круг юнит с шансом примерно в свою мораль в процентах ходит лишний раз (при плюсовой морали) или пропускает ход (при минусовой). Высокая мораль также немного увеличивает дальность хода и усиливает атаку, когда срабатывает; низкая - наоборот.",
              "Чтобы поднять мораль, двигайтесь к вражеской армии (+3 за ход) и убивайте вражеские стеки (большой толчок атакующему). Отход снижает мораль (-3), а когда гибнет ваш стек, остальные ваши стеки того же юнита тоже теряют мораль.",
              "Удача - от -10 до +10 и в основном защитная: удачливый стек получает меньше урона, неудачливый - больше (примерно 1% за единицу). Ваша удача также усиливает ваши способности и повышает шанс их срабатывания. Каждый круг удача получает небольшой случайный сдвиг; Luck Shield (защита) убирает этот сдвиг за небольшую цену в мораль.",
              "Сила стека пересчитывается от ценности стека на доске: опыт юнита умножается на количество живых существ и сравнивается с крупнейшим стеком. Диапазон - от 1 до 5.",
          ],
          mapTitle: "Карта не ждет вечно",
          mapParagraphs: [
              "Поле - сетка 16x16. В текущей ротации есть обычные карты, карты с лавовым центром и карты с заблокированным центром. Центральная гора может блокировать выстрелы и выдерживает 5 ударов; лавовый центр может дать смысл способностям Made of Fire.",
              "На обычных картах сужение идет примерно каждые 3 круга. На картах с заблокированным центром - каждые 4 круга. Если команды не сближаются и не наносят урон, игра может добавить дополнительное сужение.",
              "После 12-го круга начинается Армагеддон: четыре волны урона постепенно превращают затянутый бой в финал.",
          ],
          examplesTitle: "Мини-шпаргалка по ролям",
          examples: [
              "Black Dragon и Angel показывают силу крупных летающих финишеров, но им нужно место для 2x2 тела.",
              "Medusa, Arbalester и Gargantuan учат уважать линии стрельбы, боезапас и дистанцию.",
              "Satyr и Ogre Mage напоминают, что книга заклинаний часто важнее прямого урона.",
              "Pegasus, Griffin, Peasant и Valkyrie доказывают, что ауры выигрывают бои еще до первого удара.",
          ],
          finalTitle: "Как играть лучше уже в следующей партии",
          finalItems: [
              "Начните с плана фракции: какие 2/4/6 юнитов включат нужную синергию?",
              "Ставьте дальников так, чтобы первый вражеский рывок не выключил им стрельбу.",
              "Не тратьте Hourglass автоматически. Ждать стоит только ради конкретного следующего хода.",
              "Следите за сужением карты с первого круга, а не когда край уже стал дырой.",
          ],
      }
    : {
          eyebrow: "Game rules",
          title: "How to play Heroes of Crypto",
          description:
              "Build a compact army, place it on a 16x16 battlefield, then win through positioning, faction synergies, morale, spells, and a map that keeps closing in. This guide follows the real shared TypeScript fight engine used by the browser client.",
          primaryCta: "Play",
          secondaryCta: "Browse units",
          heroLabel: "Example combat units",
          stats: [
              { value: String(unitCount), label: "public roster units" },
              { value: String(factionUnits.length), label: "playable factions" },
              { value: String(abilityCount), label: "unit abilities" },
          ],
          loopTitle: "The match in one minute",
          loopIntro:
              "Read a match as a chain of visible decisions. You are not watching a black-box simulation: player actions go through the shared rules engine, then the browser client renders the events on the board.",
          phases: [
              {
                  title: "1. Draft",
                  text: "Build a tight roster by level: two level-1 units, two level-2 units, one level-3 unit, and one level-4 unit. Bans and reveals help manage hidden information.",
              },
              {
                  title: "2. Upgrade and synergize",
                  text: "Before the fight, spend up to 7 augment points and choose faction bonuses when your army reaches 2, 4, or 6 units from the same faction.",
              },
              {
                  title: "3. Place",
                  text: "Put stacks inside your deployment zone. Large creatures need a 2x2 footprint, ranged units need lanes, and aura units need friends inside their real range.",
              },
              {
                  title: "4. Fight",
                  text: "The active unit moves, attacks, casts, waits on Hourglass, or ends its turn. After the action resolves, the engine selects the next unit.",
              },
          ],
          winTitle: "The goal is simple: keep your army on the board",
          winParagraphs: [
              "Each unit on the board is a stack, not a single model. Damage burns through the current body in that stack, then starts killing the next one. When the stack has no living bodies left, it shatters off the board.",
              "You win when the enemy has no living stacks. If both sides stall, the game applies pressure by narrowing the map, turning outer cells into holes, and eventually starting Armageddon after lap 12.",
          ],
          readBoard: [
              "Watch the turn queue, not only the active unit.",
              "Keep ranged units out of melee contact: adjacent pressure can shut down shooting.",
              "Respect the edge. Narrowing tries to push a stack inward first, but if there is no legal space, the stack dies.",
          ],
          draftTitle: "Draft: pick a plan, not just portraits",
          draftParagraphs: [
              "Conceptually every unit pulls roughly the same weight in your army: a weaker creature simply arrives as a bigger stack, so no single unit is just 'better' than another. Fights are won by your plan and how your units synergize — not by raw stats or flashy abilities.",
              "Unit level matters, but it is not the whole game. A low-level unit can unlock the right synergy, carry an aura, bring control, or give your army a spellbook.",
              "The public roster is currently focused on four playable factions: Chaos, Life, Might, and Nature. Across them you get melee fighters, ranged units, spellcasters, flyers, large 2x2 creatures, and utility pieces with auras.",
          ],
          draftNotes: [
              "The baseline draft pool by level is 2/2/1/1.",
              "A level can only be banned if enough units of that level remain available.",
              "Reveal is best when knowing the opponent's threat matters more than taking another unknown slot.",
          ],
          unitsTitle: "How to read a unit",
          unitStats: [
              { label: "HP", text: "health of one body inside the stack" },
              { label: "Damage", text: "base attack spread before armor, luck, and modifiers" },
              { label: "Speed", text: "a major input into turn order inside each lap" },
              { label: "Steps", text: "how far the unit can move on its turn" },
              { label: "Shots", text: "ammo for ranged attacks, when the unit has a ranged attack" },
              { label: "Magic resist", text: "chance to resist debuffs and magical effects" },
          ],
          upgradesTitle: "Team upgrades: 7 points, real tradeoffs",
          upgradesIntro:
              "Augments are not cosmetics. They change deployment size, durability, ranged plans, melee damage, and tempo before the first unit acts.",
          upgrades: [
              {
                  icon: "/assets/images/units/abilities/board_augment_256.webp",
                  title: "Placement",
                  text: "Expands deployment. The starting tier limits how many stacks can be fielded; the highest tier opens the baseline cap of 8 stacks before Nature bonuses.",
              },
              {
                  icon: "/assets/images/units/abilities/armor_augment_256.webp",
                  title: "Armor",
                  text: "+6%, +13%, or +21% team armor. Strong when your army needs to survive first contact.",
              },
              {
                  icon: "/assets/images/units/abilities/might_augment_256.webp",
                  title: "Might",
                  text: "+8%, +17%, or +27% melee attack. This is for armies that intend to fight up close.",
              },
              {
                  icon: "/assets/images/units/abilities/sniper_augment_256.webp",
                  title: "Sniper",
                  text: "+7/15/24% ranged attack and +20/40/70% shot distance. Take it when firing lanes are your win condition.",
              },
              {
                  icon: "/assets/images/units/abilities/movement_augment_256.webp",
                  title: "Movement",
                  text: "+1 or +2 movement steps. Sometimes one extra cell is worth more than another damage buff.",
              },
          ],
          synergiesTitle: "Faction synergies: 2, 4, and 6 units",
          synergiesIntro:
              "When you field 2/4/6 units from the same faction, that faction reaches synergy level 1/2/3. For each faction, you choose one of two bonuses.",
          synergyLevels: "Power by level",
          synergies: [
              {
                  faction: "Life",
                  icon: "/assets/images/units/factions/life_128.webp",
                  options: ["Supply: +6% / +12% / +19% bodies in each stack", "Morale & luck: +6/+2, +13/+5, +20/+9"],
              },
              {
                  faction: "Chaos",
                  icon: "/assets/images/units/factions/chaos_128.webp",
                  options: ["Movement: +1 / +2 / +3 cells", "Break on attack: 8% / 13% / 19% chance to shut off abilities"],
              },
              {
                  faction: "Might",
                  icon: "/assets/images/units/factions/might_128.webp",
                  options: ["Aura range: +1 / +2 / +3 cells", "Stack abilities power: +5% / +8% / +12%"],
              },
              {
                  faction: "Nature",
                  icon: "/assets/images/units/factions/nature_128.webp",
                  options: ["Board units: +1 / +2 / +3 fielded stacks", "Flying armor: +10% / +20% / +30%"],
              },
          ],
          placementTitle: "Placement: many fights are won before the first hit",
          placementParagraphs: [
              "Choose a unit from the roster, set the stack amount, and place it in your allowed deployment zone. You can move placed stacks, clone the selected stack, delete it, and tune the final shape before starting the fight.",
              "Large units occupy 2x2 cells. They are powerful pieces, but they ask for space: harder to route through a crowded center and harder to save when narrowing starts.",
              "Before pressing start, check three things: who is inside your auras, who can be reached on the first turn, and where your ranged units will stand if the enemy dives them.",
          ],
          turnsTitle: "Turns: one decision, then the queue moves",
          turnActions: [
              {
                  title: "Move",
                  text: "The path must be legal and fit inside the unit's Steps. Moving closer to the nearest enemy raises morale; backing away can lower it.",
              },
              {
                  title: "Melee attack",
                  text: "The unit must stand next to the target. A ranged unit forced into melee hits at reduced damage unless an ability covers it.",
              },
              {
                  title: "Ranged attack",
                  text: "You need shots, a valid line, and no melee lock. Long shots are reduced by a range divisor up to x8 unless Sniper avoids the penalty.",
              },
              {
                  title: "Spellbook",
                  text: "Spellbook units cast buffs, debuffs, healing, mass effects, summons, and position tricks. Magic resist and mind resistance can stop effects.",
              },
              {
                  title: "Hourglass",
                  text: "The unit waits and comes back later in the queue. It costs morale, but it can turn a bad action now into a better action later.",
              },
              {
                  title: "Luck Shield / Skip",
                  text: "Luck Shield (defend) clears this turn's random luck swing and ends the turn, for a small morale cost. A forced skip also ends the turn and costs morale; ending your turn normally after acting costs nothing.",
              },
          ],
          combatTitle: "Combat, without the formula sheet",
          combatParagraphs: [
              "Damage depends on attack, living bodies in the stack, target armor, luck, range distance, selected attack type, and active abilities. That is why the same unit can hit very differently from two different board states.",
              "Responses exist. Melee and ranged units can answer an attack if they have not already replied, are not blocked by an effect, and can actually reach the attacker.",
              "Abilities give fights their character: Lucky Strike can spike damage, Stun and Blindness break tempo, Petrifying Gaze can finish a target, Fire Shield returns damage, and Range Null Field shuts down shooting around it.",
          ],
          moraleTitle: "Morale, luck, and stack power",
          moraleItems: [
              "Morale runs from -20 to +20. Each lap a unit rolls about its morale value in percent to act an extra time (positive morale) or be skipped (negative morale). High morale also nudges movement range and, when it procs, boosts attack; low morale does the opposite.",
              "To build morale, advance toward the enemy army (+3 per move) and kill enemy stacks (a big push for the attacker). Retreating costs morale (-3), and when one of your stacks dies, your other stacks of that same unit lose morale too.",
              "Luck runs from -10 to +10 and is mostly defensive: a lucky stack takes less damage, an unlucky one takes more (about 1% per point). Your own luck also makes your abilities stronger and more likely to fire. Luck gets a small random swing each lap; Luck Shield (defend) clears that swing for a small morale cost.",
              "Stack power is recalculated from a stack's board value: unit experience times living amount, compared with the largest stack present. It ranges from 1 to 5.",
          ],
          mapTitle: "The map does not wait forever",
          mapParagraphs: [
              "The board is a 16x16 grid. The current random map rotation includes normal, lava-center, and block-center maps. The center mountain can block shots and has 5 hits; lava-center maps make Made of Fire matter.",
              "Normal maps narrow roughly every 3 laps. Block-center maps narrow every 4 laps. If neither army closes distance or deals damage, the engine can add extra narrowing pressure.",
              "After lap 12, Armageddon starts: four damage waves gradually force a stalled fight to end.",
          ],
          examplesTitle: "Role cheat sheet",
          examples: [
              "Black Dragon and Angel show what large flying finishers can do, but both need room for a 2x2 body.",
              "Medusa, Arbalester, and Gargantuan teach firing lanes, ammo, and range distance.",
              "Satyr and Ogre Mage are reminders that a spellbook can matter more than raw damage.",
              "Pegasus, Griffin, Peasant, and Valkyrie prove that aura placement wins fights before the first attack lands.",
          ],
          finalTitle: "How to play better next match",
          finalItems: [
              "Start with a faction plan: which 2/4/6 units unlock the synergy you actually want?",
              "Place ranged units so the enemy's first dive does not shut off their shooting.",
              "Do not press Hourglass automatically. Wait only when you know what better turn you are creating.",
              "Track the narrowing map from lap one, not when the edge is already a hole.",
          ],
      };

const factionDescriptions: Record<Language, Record<FactionName, string>> = {
    en: {
        Chaos: "Disruption, fire pressure, nasty ranged tricks, and Break plans.",
        Life: "Reliable bodies, armor, resurrection, morale, and formation support.",
        Might: "Direct damage, strong melee pressure, aura scaling, and heavy finishers.",
        Nature: "Mobility, flyers, summons, camouflage, and board-control tools.",
        Death: "Reserved and summon-facing pieces in the current public data.",
    },
    ru: {
        Chaos: "Давление, огонь, неприятные стрелковые трюки и планы через срыв атак.",
        Life: "Надежные стеки, броня, воскрешение, мораль и поддержка построения.",
        Might: "Прямой урон, сильное давление в ближнем бою, усиление аур и тяжелые финишеры.",
        Nature: "Мобильность, летающие юниты, призыв, маскировка и контроль поля.",
        Death: "Резервные и связанные с призывом существа в текущих публичных данных.",
    },
};
---

<section class="rules-hero">
    <img class="rules-hero-bg" src="/assets/images/preview_game.webp" alt="" width="1200" height="630" />
    <div class="rules-hero-shade"></div>
    <div class="page-shell rules-hero-shell">
        <div class="rules-hero-copy">
            <p class="eyebrow">{copy.eyebrow}</p>
            <h1>{copy.title}</h1>
            <p>{copy.description}</p>
            <div class="rules-hero-actions">
                <a class="button primary" href={playHref}>
                    <img src="/assets/icons/navbar/joystick.svg" alt="" width="22" height="22" />
                    {copy.primaryCta}
                </a>
                <a class="button secondary" href={unitsHref}>{copy.secondaryCta}</a>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rules-showcase" aria-label={copy.heroLabel}>
            <div class="rules-board-shot rules-hero-board" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rules-hero-board-grid">
                    {
                        Array.from({ length: 64 }).map((_, i) => (
                            <span
                                class:list={[
                                    {
                                        "is-deploy-left": i % 8 < 2,
                                        "is-deploy-right": i % 8 > 5,
                                        "is-center": i === 27 || i === 28 || i === 35 || i === 36,
                                        "is-hole": i < 8 || i > 55,
                                    },
                                ]}
                            />
                        ))
                    }
                </div>
                <img class="rules-hero-piece dragon" src="/assets/images/units/units/black_dragon_512.webp" alt="" width="512" height="512" loading="eager" />
                <img class="rules-hero-piece angel" src="/assets/images/units/units/angel_512.webp" alt="" width="512" height="512" loading="eager" />
                <img class="rules-hero-piece arbalester" src="/assets/images/units/units/arbalester_512.webp" alt="" width="512" height="512" loading="eager" />
                <img class="rules-hero-piece pegasus" src="/assets/images/units/units/pegasus_512.webp" alt="" width="512" height="512" loading="eager" />
                <img class="rules-hero-piece medusa" src="/assets/images/units/units/medusa_512.webp" alt="" width="512" height="512" loading="eager" />
            </div>
            <div class="rules-unit-line">
                {
                    heroUnits.map((unit) => (
                        <a
                            href={unitsHref}
                            class="rules-hero-unit"
                            style={`--faction: ${factionColors[unit.faction]}`}
                            aria-label={`${unit.name}, ${factionLabel(unit.faction)}`}
                        >
                            <img src={unit.icon} alt="" width="512" height="512" loading="eager" />
                            <span>{unit.name}</span>
                        </a>
                    ))
                }
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="rules-stat-strip" aria-label={copy.eyebrow}>
    <div class="page-shell rules-stats">
        {copy.stats.map((stat) => <div><strong>{stat.value}</strong><span>{stat.label}</span></div>)}
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section rules-section">
    <div class="page-shell">
        <div class="section-heading">
            <p class="eyebrow">{isRu ? "Цикл боя" : "Fight loop"}</p>
            <h2>{copy.loopTitle}</h2>
            <p>{copy.loopIntro}</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rules-phase-grid">
            {copy.phases.map((phase) => <article class="rules-card"><h3>{phase.title}</h3><p>{phase.text}</p></article>)}
        </div>

        <div class="rules-facts" aria-label={isRu ? "Ключевые числа" : "Key numbers"}>
            {
                quickFacts.map((fact) => (
                    <div class="rules-fact" tabindex="0">
                        <strong>{fact.value}</strong>
                        <span>{fact.label}</span>
                        <span class="rules-fact-tip" role="tooltip">
                            {fact.tip}
                        </span>
                    </div>
                ))
            }
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section rules-band">
    <div class="page-shell rules-two-col">
        <div class="rules-copy-block">
            <p class="eyebrow">{isRu ? "Победа" : "Victory"}</p>
            <h2>{copy.winTitle}</h2>
            {copy.winParagraphs.map((paragraph) => <p>{paragraph}</p>)}
        </div>
        <div class="rules-note-list">
            {copy.readBoard.map((item) => <p>{item}</p>)}
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section rules-section">
    <div class="page-shell rules-two-col wide">
        <div class="rules-copy-block">
            <p class="eyebrow">{isRu ? "Драфт" : "Draft"}</p>
            <h2>{copy.draftTitle}</h2>
            {copy.draftParagraphs.map((paragraph) => <p>{paragraph}</p>)}
            <ul class="rules-clean-list">
                {copy.draftNotes.map((note) => <li>{note}</li>)}
            </ul>
            <div class="rules-level-table" aria-label={isRu ? "Драфт по уровням" : "Draft by level"}>
                <div class="rules-level-row rules-level-head">
                    <span>{isRu ? "Уровень" : "Level"}</span>
                    <span>{isRu ? "Берёте" : "You draft"}</span>
                    <span>{isRu ? "В пуле" : "In pool"}</span>
                </div>
                {
                    levelRows.map((row) => (
                        <div class="rules-level-row">
                            <span>{isRu ? "Ур." : "Lv"} {row.level}</span>
                            <span>×{row.draft}</span>
                            <span>{row.available}</span>
                        </div>
                    ))
                }
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="rules-faction-grid">
            {
                factionUnits.map((faction) => (
                    <a href={unitsHref} class="rules-faction" style={`--faction: ${faction.color}`}>
                        <span class="rules-faction-head">
                            <img src={faction.icon} alt="" width="34" height="34" loading="lazy" />
                            <strong>{factionLabel(faction.faction)}</strong>
                            <em>{faction.units.length}</em>
                        </span>
                        <span>{factionDescriptions[lang][faction.faction]}</span>
                    </a>
                ))
            }
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section rules-band">
    <div class="page-shell">
        <div class="section-heading">
            <p class="eyebrow">{isRu ? "Карточка юнита" : "Unit card"}</p>
            <h2>{copy.unitsTitle}</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="rules-unit-reader">
            <div class="rules-example-units">
                {
                    exampleUnits.map((unit) => (
                        <a href={unitsHref} class="rules-example-unit" style={`--faction: ${factionColors[unit.faction]}`}>
                            <img src={unit.icon} alt="" width="512" height="512" loading="lazy" />
                            <span>
                                <strong>{unit.name}</strong>
                                <em>
                                    {attackLabels[unit.attackType as keyof typeof attackLabels] ?? unit.attackType} ·{" "}
                                    {movementLabels[unit.movementType as keyof typeof movementLabels] ?? unit.movementType}
                                </em>
                            </span>
                        </a>
                    ))
                }
            </div>
            <div class="rules-stat-reader">
                {copy.unitStats.map((stat) => <div><strong>{stat.label}</strong><p>{stat.text}</p></div>)}
                <div class="rules-role-row">
                    {
                        Object.entries(roleCounts).map(([role, count]) => (
                            <span>
                                <strong>{count}</strong>
                                {attackLabels[role as keyof typeof attackLabels] ?? role}
                            </span>
                        ))
                    }
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section rules-section">
    <div class="page-shell">
        <div class="section-heading">
            <p class="eyebrow">{isRu ? "Апгрейды" : "Augments"}</p>
            <h2>{copy.upgradesTitle}</h2>
            <p>{copy.upgradesIntro}</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rules-aug-table" aria-label={isRu ? "Уровни апгрейдов" : "Augment tiers"}>
            <div class="rules-aug-row rules-aug-head">
                <span>{isRu ? "Апгрейд" : "Augment"}</span>
                <span>{isRu ? "Ур. 1" : "Tier 1"}</span>
                <span>{isRu ? "Ур. 2" : "Tier 2"}</span>
                <span>{isRu ? "Ур. 3" : "Tier 3"}</span>
            </div>
            {
                augmentTable.map((aug) => (
                    <div class="rules-aug-row">
                        <span class="rules-aug-name">
                            <img src={aug.icon} alt="" width="256" height="256" loading="lazy" />
                            <span>
                                <strong>{aug.name}</strong>
                                <em>{aug.note}</em>
                            </span>
                        </span>
                        {aug.tiers.map((tier) => <span class="rules-aug-tier">{tier}</span>)}
                    </div>
                ))
            }
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section rules-band">
    <div class="page-shell">
        <div class="section-heading">
            <p class="eyebrow">{isRu ? "Синергии" : "Synergies"}</p>
            <h2>{copy.synergiesTitle}</h2>
            <p>{copy.synergiesIntro}</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rules-synergy-grid">
            {
                copy.synergies.map((synergy) => (
                    <article
                        class="rules-synergy"
